{
  "text": "[12] At the upper level, the westward flowing EIC, centered on the equator, the SICC and NICC centered 2\u00b0S and 2\u00b0N respectively, both flowing eastward and the two westward mean currents centered 4\u00b0S and 4\u00b0N, called South and North Equatorial Intermediate Currents (SEIC and NEIC [CITATION_1] ]) are strong features of the intermediate equatorial circulation with peak mean velocities exceeding 10 cm s",
  "correct_citation": {
